Item ID5295

Ranarr seeds are planted in herb patches, requiring 32 Farming, to grow grimy ranarr weeds. They can be obtained from monsters, pickpocketing Master Farmers, high level gambles from the Barbarian Assault minigame, larran's big chest, or from Managing Miscellania if residents are assigned to Farming.

Herb running ranarr seeds is profitable if disease chance is minimised and yield is maximised. Use ultracompost, or the enhanced Fertile Soil spell, to reduce disease and increase the average yield. Plant anima seeds, iasor to reduce disease chance, attas to increase yield. Equip magic secateurs and the Farming cape when harvesting to increase yield.

It is also recommended to utilise disease free patches on top of Troll Stronghold after completing My Arm's Big Adventure, the Hosidius patch after having at least 50% Hosidius favour, and the herb patch in Weiss, which is usable after building the Fire of Nourishment fire pit.

Note: A nearby gardener will not watch over your growing herb.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
23 July 2020
(update | poll)

The appearance of herbs planted in herb patches now match the herb's appearance in the player's inventory.

9 January 2020
(update | poll)

Players can now dig up healthy herb patches before they're fully grown. To prevent players from gaining experience repeatedly by planting and digging up herb seeds, the experience usually gained from planting them are now given when harvesting them, alongside the usual harvesting experience.

8 February 2018
(update | poll)

The value was changed from 19 to 50 so that it would appear above less valuable seeds when on the ground.

11 July 2005
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Herb seed" to "Ranarr seed".
  • The item's examine was changed from "Farming skill coming in July!" to "A ranarr seed - plant in a herb patch."
